			<div class="content" id="post-content-693508">
									

<p>There are various issues of terminology (any sensible human would describe the item as a "bead", besides, if it's not crystalline, then how could it possibly be a gem?), technical (many non-flowering plants do not produce seeds <em>per se</em>, and quite a few do produce structures analogous to flowers) and structure/style (probably too much censoring in the final paragraph). Overall, though, I like it.</p>

