														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-694270">
									

<p>Not all plants produce seeds, no, but they do all produce some form of dispersal unit. Flowering plants have fruit. Gymnosperms (pines etc.) have seeds but no fruit. Ferns, fernlike plants, and mosses have spores. Even liverworts produce tiny scraps of tissues called gemmae, which are splashed around by rain and sprout into more liverworts when they land someplace hospitable.</p>
<p>If you like, with your permission, I could edit this for botanical accuracy. Botany's my area of expertise; I could have fun with this.</p>

